reviews.text: I was searching for a salad spot on Google and came across this place today‚ÄîI‚Äôm so glad I did. Since I love salads, I grabbed two: one for lunch and one for dinner. The menu has great options, the customer service was excellent, and the atmosphere is warm and welcoming. Best of all, my salad was absolutely delicious.

This salad was so huge and fresh. Worth the money. And didn‚Äôt miss any of my add ons. Definitely will order again. And it was tossed with vegetables all the way through instead of just on top. That‚Äôs the best part and freshness!
This was once of the most delicious Caesar salad I‚Äôve ever had. Customer Service and atmosphere was amazing. I will definitely be returning ‚ù§Ô∏è

Ordered the "Can't be Beet" salad and it is delicious!  Very large salad full of Spinach, avocado, beets, craisins, feta, mandarin oranges & walnuts.  I added a protein of salmon and Honey Peanut Butter Vinaigrette dressing on the side.  Loved every bite!!  Large enough for 2 meals, maybe 3!  I ate as much as I could for my lunch and have more than half leftover for dinner tonight!  You should definitely check this gem out -- off the beaten path in Cordova near Germantown Parkway and Dexter.  Great for takeout, order ahead online and they will have it ready for you when you get there.  Hours are limited right now... I think they close at 6 on weeknights and aren't open on weekends.  But definitely worth checking out!  I will be back!!!!

The quality at this place can be hit or miss‚Äîsome days are excellent, while others fall short. Today, I was concerned about the cleanliness when I noticed several flies landing on the salad toppings. I recommend that they use covers on all their toppings. Additionally, the salad was unevenly chopped, leaving large chunks. The picture illustrates one of the flies resting on the dried onions.
